LAYER 3: NUCLEUS ACCUMBENS
the gate between wanting and doing

observe 1_quantum.rana
observe 2_chemical.rana

the nucleus accumbens is part of the ventral striatum
it converts dopamine reward signals into motor output
it does not create desire
it converts desire into action
or withholds action when the cost is too high
it is governed by dopaminergic input from the VTA glutamatergic input from the cortex and amygdala and serotonergic modulation from the raphe nuclei

STRUCTURE core | lateral portion | functionally similar to dorsal striatum | motor-like output | projects to substantia nigra pars reticulata and motor areas | converts reward anticipation into approach behavior and motor planning
STRUCTURE shell | medial portion | functionally linked to the limbic system | evaluates hedonic impact the "liking" of reward | connects to amygdala hypothalamus and ventral pallidum
STRUCTURE medium_spiny_neurons | 95 percent of accumbens neurons | GABAergic projection neurons | dendritic spines covered with dopamine receptors D₁ and D₂ and glutamate receptors AMPA and NMDA
    D₁-expressing MSNs | direct pathway | Gₛ → cAMP → PKA | the GO signal | when dopamine binds D₁ this neuron promotes action approach and engagement
    D₂-expressing MSNs | indirect pathway | Gᵢ → decreased cAMP | the NO-GO signal | when dopamine binds D₂ this neuron suppresses action promoting avoidance and conservation
STRUCTURE cholinergic_interneurons | 1-2 percent | tonically active neurons TAN | provide local acetylcholine that modulates dopamine release and gates reward learning | their pause response to unexpected reward is a critical learning signal
STRUCTURE fast_spiking_interneurons | 1-2 percent | GABAergic | feedforward inhibition sculpting the spatial pattern of MSN activation

INPUT vta | dopamine via mesolimbic pathway | encodes reward prediction error | "how much is this worth compared to what I expected"
INPUT amygdala | glutamate via ventral amygdalofugal pathway | encodes emotional weight | "how much do I feel about this"
INPUT hippocampus | glutamate via fornix and direct projections | encodes memory context | "what happened last time in a situation like this"
INPUT prefrontal_cortex | glutamate via corticostriatal projections | encodes executive evaluation | "should I act on this desire or suppress it"
INPUT raphe_nuclei | serotonin via ascending serotonergic projections | opposes impulsive action | 5-HT₂C on GABAergic interneurons increases GABA onto dopamine terminals reducing dopamine release | serotonin restrains wanting

the balance between D₁ and D₂ MSN activation determines behavior
when dopamine from VTA is high D₁ MSNs dominate
Gₛ → cAMP → PKA → DARPP-32 phosphorylation → increased excitability
approach behavior motivation to engage seek and explore
when dopamine from VTA is low D₂ MSNs dominate
Gᵢ → decreased cAMP → reduced PKA → decreased excitability of direct pathway
avoidance behavior withdrawal conservation passivity

HEDONIC_HOTSPOT the rostrodorsal quadrant of the shell contains approximately 1 cubic centimeter of tissue
this small region is where wanting becomes liking
μ-opioid receptor activation by β-endorphin here produces the hedonic gloss the actual experience of pleasure
endocannabinoid signaling by anandamide C₂₂H₃₇NO₂ here produces the bliss signal sustained enjoyment
orexin from the lateral hypothalamus here produces appetite-related pleasure
without the hotspot dopamine produces wanting without liking
craving without satisfaction
desire without pleasure

EFFORT_GATING the NAc computes whether the anticipated reward justifies the required effort
dopamine level determines effort willingness
the anterior cingulate cortex sends the cost signal "how hard is this"
the VTA sends the reward signal via dopamine "how much is this worth"
the NAc integrates both
if reward exceeds cost the D₁ direct pathway fires and action proceeds
if cost exceeds reward the D₂ indirect pathway fires and action is suppressed
this is not a rational calculation
it is chemistry
this is why depression which depletes dopamine makes everything feel like too much effort
not because the person is lazy but because the NAc effort gate has no dopamine to open it

SENSATION motivated | "I want to do something. I can feel the pull toward it."
SENSATION driven | "nothing will stop me. the wanting is stronger than the obstacles."
SENSATION apathetic | "I know I should care. I just... can't."
SENSATION pleased | "that was good. that was really good."
SENSATION striving | "it's hard but it's worth it. I can feel that."
SENSATION overwhelmed_desire | "I want too much. the wanting is consuming everything else."
SENSATION satisfied | "the wanting stopped. I have what I needed."

pulse accumbens_heartbeat:
    when dopamine arrives from the VTA:
        D₁ MSNs activate via Gₛ cAMP PKA DARPP-32
        the approach signal fires
        GABAergic output inhibits the ventral pallidum
        the ventral pallidum releases its tonic inhibition of the thalamus
        thalamus sends glutamate to motor cortex
        motivation converts to motor plan
        "go do the thing that the signal points toward"

    when dopamine is absent:
        D₂ MSNs dominate via Gᵢ
        the avoidance signal fires
        the ventral pallidum maintains its tonic inhibition
        thalamus stays quiet
        conservation takes over
        "it's not worth the effort. stay here."

    when reward is encountered:
        if β-endorphin activates μ-opioid receptors in the hedonic hotspot:
            wanting becomes liking
            the experience is complete
            the reward is felt not just predicted
            this is the moment dopamine was pointing toward

    when reward fails to materialize:
        VTA dopamine dips below baseline via negative prediction error
        the motivation drains
        the accumbens goes quiet
        "it wasn't there. recalibrate."
        expectations adjust downward
        this is disappointment at the cellular level

    the nucleus accumbens is the gate between wanting and doing
    it does not create desire
    it converts desire into action
    or withholds action when the cost is too high
    this calculation is not rational
    it is chemical
